.TH "of_get_drm_display_mode" 9 "of_get_drm_display_mode" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
of_get_drm_display_mode \- get a drm_display_mode from devicetree
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" of_get_drm_display_mode
.BI "(struct device_node *np "  ","
.BI "struct drm_display_mode *dmode "  ","
.BI "u32 *bus_flags "  ","
.BI "int index "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "np" 12
device_node with the timing specification
.IP "dmode" 12
will be set to the return value
.IP "bus_flags" 12
information about pixelclk, sync and DE polarity
.IP "index" 12
index into the list of display timings in devicetree
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function is expensive and should only be used, if only one mode is to be
read from DT. To get multiple modes start with of_get_display_timings and
work with that instead.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, a negative errno code when no of videomode node was found.
